    {
      "id": "E:note:row717576:1",
      "kind": "note_sentence",
      "display": "42F OSH transer with severe lupus with    cryoglobulinemia vasculitis (on Cellce",
      "code": null,
      "value": null,
      "unit": null,
      "effective": null,
      "source_ref": "note:row717576#s1",
      "text": "42F OSH transer with severe lupus with    cryoglobulinemia vasculitis (on Cellcept, Prednisone, recently being tx    for a flare), CAD 3VD s/p multiple MI's and stenting (EF 20%) s/p V Fib    arrest (date unknown) with AICD, trace MR, chronic pain (on Methadone)    that presents altered mental status and hypoxia."
    },
    {
      "id": "E:note:row717576:2",
      "kind": "note_sentence",
      "display": "At the OSH the patient    remained delerious and confused noted to be \"rhyming w",
      "code": null,
      "value": null,
      "unit": null,
      "effective": null,
      "source_ref": "note:row717576#s2",
      "text": "At the OSH the patient    remained delerious and confused noted to be \"rhyming words\"."
    },
    {
      "id": "E:note:row717576:3",
      "kind": "note_sentence",
      "display": "OSH team    felt believed some of her symptoms may have been secondary to narcot",
      "code": null,
      "value": null,
      "unit": null,
      "effective": null,
      "source_ref": "note:row717576#s3",
      "text": "OSH team    felt believed some of her symptoms may have been secondary to narcotic    and/or benzo withdrwal (as evidence by flushing and diaphoresis) and    thus, she was also receiving Morphine IV and Valium q6H."
    },
    {
      "id": "E:note:row717576:4",
      "kind": "note_sentence",
      "display": "Given a    concern of sepsis in a patient with MS changes and tachycardia the pt",
      "code": null,
      "value": null,
      "unit": null,
      "effective": null,
      "source_ref": "note:row717576#s4",
      "text": "Given a    concern of sepsis in a patient with MS changes and tachycardia the pt    was given Vancomycin 1gm IVx1 and Zosyn 3.375mg IVx1 on [**2108-12-23**]    (nursing report listed Cefepime 2gm IV however no record seen in med    rec)."
    },
    {
      "id": "E:note:row717576:5",
      "kind": "note_sentence",
      "display": "The pt remained afebrile while at [**Hospital3 519**] with all    cultures NGTD.",
      "code": null,
      "value": null,
      "unit": null,
      "effective": null,
      "source_ref": "note:row717576#s5",
      "text": "The pt remained afebrile while at [**Hospital3 519**] with all    cultures NGTD."
    },
    {
      "id": "E:note:row717576:6",
      "kind": "note_sentence",
      "display": "In addition the pt's prednisone was changed to    Methylprednisolone 125mg IV q8",
      "code": null,
      "value": null,
      "unit": null,
      "effective": null,
      "source_ref": "note:row717576#s6",
      "text": "In addition the pt's prednisone was changed to    Methylprednisolone 125mg IV q8H (unclear if pt received dose)."
    },
    {
      "id": "E:note:row717576:7",
      "kind": "note_sentence",
      "display": "Altered mental status (not Delirium)    Assessment:    Pt was agitated on and of",
      "code": null,
      "value": null,
      "unit": null,
      "effective": null,
      "source_ref": "note:row717576#s7",
      "text": "Altered mental status (not Delirium)    Assessment:    Pt was agitated on and off today alternating with becoming nearly    unresponsive."
    },
    {
      "id": "E:note:row717576:8",
      "kind": "note_sentence",
      "display": "After 10mg of IV valium she would often wake up, tell me    where she was and th",
      "code": null,
      "value": null,
      "unit": null,
      "effective": null,
      "source_ref": "note:row717576#s8",
      "text": "After 10mg of IV valium she would often wake up, tell me    where she was and that it was [**2108-12-14**], she admitted to pain and    anxiety."
    },
    {
      "id": "E:note:row717576:9",
      "kind": "note_sentence",
      "display": "Through the day her resp rate cont to increase up to 60/min    with periods of a",
      "code": null,
      "value": null,
      "unit": null,
      "effective": null,
      "source_ref": "note:row717576#s9",
      "text": "Through the day her resp rate cont to increase up to 60/min    with periods of apnea    Action:    Given intermittand doses of valium, morphine, and dilaudid  but not    nearly the benzo and narcotic use she had at home."
    },
    {
      "id": "E:note:row717576:10",
      "kind": "note_sentence",
      "display": "She was seen by    neurology, EEG done, finally intubated for tachypnea and to a",
      "code": null,
      "value": null,
      "unit": null,
      "effective": null,
      "source_ref": "note:row717576#s10",
      "text": "She was seen by    neurology, EEG done, finally intubated for tachypnea and to allow us to    do an LP and place a new CL."
    },
    {
      "id": "E:note:row717576:11",
      "kind": "note_sentence",
      "display": "Response:    Pt is sedated on fent and versed    Plan:    Will need to have her ",
      "code": null,
      "value": null,
      "unit": null,
      "effective": null,
      "source_ref": "note:row717576#s11",
      "text": "Response:    Pt is sedated on fent and versed    Plan:    Will need to have her sedation decreased to follow her MS, follow for    withdraw of benzos and narcotics    Tachycardia, Other    Assessment:    Pt with a HR of 160 this am, pt agitated    Action:    Given 5 mg of lopressor x2 and 10 mg of valium, cardiac echo was done    Response:    Her HR decreased to the 120s after these meds but it did not last."
    },
    {
      "id": "E:note:row717576:12",
      "kind": "note_sentence",
      "display": "After she was intubated and sedated her HR decreased to the low 120s    Plan:   ",
      "code": null,
      "value": null,
      "unit": null,
      "effective": null,
      "source_ref": "note:row717576#s12",
      "text": "After she was intubated and sedated her HR decreased to the low 120s    Plan:    Cont to follow    Systemic Lupus Erythematosus (SLE)    Assessment:    Pt with  known severe lupus, vasculitis    Action:    Response:    Plan:    Peripheral vascular disease (PVD) with critical limb ischemia    Assessment:    Action:    Response:    Plan:    Pain control (acute pain, chronic pain)    Assessment:    Action:    Response:    Plan:    Coagulopathy    Assessment:    Action:    Response:    Plan:"
    }
  ],
